<item>
            <title>[LU-7567] lfs_changelog() misprints timestamps</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7567</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;cr_time&lt;/tt&gt; field of a changelog record is &lt;tt&gt;(secs &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 30) + nsecs&lt;/tt&gt;. So &lt;tt&gt;lfs_changelog()&lt;/tt&gt; should use &quot;.09d&quot; when printing the fractional part. Instead it uses &quot;.06d&quot;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;		secs = rec-&amp;gt;cr_time &amp;gt;&amp;gt; 30;
                gmtime_r(&amp;amp;secs, &amp;amp;ts);
		printf(LPU64&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; %02d%-5s %02d:%02d:%02d.%06d %04d.%02d.%02d &quot;&lt;/span&gt;
		       &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;0x%x t=&quot;&lt;/span&gt;DFID, rec-&amp;gt;cr_index, rec-&amp;gt;cr_type,
        	       changelog_type2str(rec-&amp;gt;cr_type),
                       ts.tm_hour, ts.tm_min, ts.tm_sec,
		       (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;)(rec-&amp;gt;cr_time &amp;amp; ((1&amp;lt;&amp;lt;30) - 1)),
                       ts.tm_year + 1900, ts.tm_mon + 1, ts.tm_mday,
		       rec-&amp;gt;cr_flags &amp;amp; CLF_FLAGMASK, PFID(&amp;amp;rec-&amp;gt;cr_tfid));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
